# Architecture Patterns

## Caching (`src/cache.ts`)
- Flat-file JSON disk cache keyed by a stable hash of the request
- All external API calls (Firecrawl, Claude) must go through the cache unless `forceRefresh: true`
- Cache dir defaults to `CACHE_DIR` env var; managed by `src/settings.ts`
- Cache files are invalidated by TTL (`SEARCH_CACHE_TTL_SECONDS`) for search results

## Extraction strategies (`src/extraction/`)
Two interchangeable strategies behind the same interface:

| Strategy | File | Description |
|----------|------|-------------|
| `bottom-up` | `extraction/bottom-up.ts` | Pass 1: extract per-source in parallel → Pass 2: synthesize all results |
| `top-down` | `extraction/top-down.ts` | Pass 1: identify key points globally → Pass 2: retrieve supporting quotes |

- Both receive `Source[]` and return `KeyPoint[]`
- Add new strategies as new files; wire them into `pipeline.ts` switch

## Prompts (`src/prompts.ts`)
- Keep all Claude prompt strings here — not inline in extraction files
- Prompts are intentionally kept identical to the Python `rnd-kpa` reference implementation

## Data models (`src/models.ts`)
All types defined as Zod schemas; TypeScript types derived via `z.infer<>`:
```
Source → KeyPoint[] (each with Quote[]) → KPAResult
```

## Pipeline orchestrator (`src/pipeline.ts`)
- Single `runKpa(query, opts)` function
- Responsible for: cache lookup → fetch sources → route to extraction strategy → cache write → return
- Keep orchestration logic here; keep side-effects (API calls, disk I/O) in their respective modules

## Error handling
- Throw typed errors from API wrappers; catch and log at the CLI/pipeline boundary
- Never swallow errors silently — always log with the pino logger before re-throwing or returning a fallback
